Online Registration & Learning Management System (LMS) built with HTML / CSS / JavaScript (no code — only ideas and structure). I’ll cover pages, user roles, features, dashboards, UX/layout, animations, data model, testing, deliverables, and stretch goals. Treat this as your project spec + design brief.

1 — Quick summary / goals

Primary goal: let students register for courses and participate in learning (lessons, assignments, quizzes), while teachers manage content and admins manage users/courses.

Must-have tech approach: HTML5 semantic markup, modular CSS (CSS variables + BEM or utility-first), vanilla JS with modular structure (ES modules). Progressive enhancement and responsive/mobile-first design.

UX goals: clear registration flow, fast content consumption, meaningful progress indicators, easy teacher workflows, clean dashboards, accessible UI.



---

2 — Users & roles (permissions)

1. Guest / Visitor

View public pages (home, about, courses list), register or log in.



2. Student

Register/login, enroll in courses, view lessons, submit assignments, take quizzes, messaging, view grades and progress.



3. Teacher / Instructor

Create/edit courses & lessons, upload materials, create assignments/quizzes, grade submissions, message students, view analytics for their courses.



4. Admin

Manage users (approve teachers), manage courses, site settings, view global analytics, moderate content and reports.




(Design role-based menus and route guards in UI.)


