4 — Page-by-page content & components (what to include)

Home / Landing

Hero with clear CTA (Register / View Courses)

Short value propositions (3 cards: “Register in minutes”, “Structured lessons”, “Track progress”)

Featured courses / categories

Quick stats (students, courses)

Testimonials / feedback

Footer: contact, social links, privacy, quick links


Courses catalog

Filters: category, level, teacher, price (if any), language, duration

Sort: popularity, newest, highest rated

Course cards: image, title, short desc, rating, teacher, enroll button


Course detail

Banner with progress/enroll CTA

Tabs: Overview | Curriculum | Instructor | Reviews | Resources

Curriculum list: modules → lessons (previewable)

Enrollment callouts & prerequisites


Registration & Login

Simple, mobile-first forms

Social login placeholders (optional)

Validation messages inline

Terms acceptance


Student dashboard

Current courses with progress bars

Upcoming deadlines / calendar

Recent announcements / messages

Quick actions (continue last lesson, submit assignment)

Badges & achievements


Teacher dashboard

Courses they teach, student counts, pending grading items

Create new course button

Quick analytics: completion, average grade, most active students


Admin dashboard

User counts, site activity, course approvals

Moderation queue

Global analytics (registrations/day, active users, storage usage)


Lesson viewer

Left: lesson list / module nav (collapsible on mobile)

Main: content area (text + images + embedded video)

Right: resources (attachments), progress checklist, discussion feed

Sticky progress bar + next/previous buttons


Assignments / Quizzes

Assignment: description, due date, upload form, submission history

Quiz: question types (MCQ, true/false), timer, immediate feedback


Messaging / Discussion

Threaded comments per lesson & private messages

Basic search and attachments



---

5 — Core features & flows (detailed)

Registration flow

Email + password (confirm), basic profile (name, university id)

Email verification

Onboarding: quick tour or “take a sample lesson” CTA


Course creation flow (teacher)

Step 1: Course metadata (title, description, category, thumbnail)

Step 2: Draft curriculum (add modules & lessons)

Step 3: Upload resources (PDF, images, video links)

Step 4: Attach assignments/quizzes and publish


Enrollment flow (student)

From course page → enroll (confirmation modal) → added to dashboard

Optional: prerequisites check


Lesson consumption

Progressive reading: collapse long sections with "Continue reading"

Inline resources, timestamped notes, downloadable files


Assignment submission & grading

Student uploads (single file or multiple), add comment

Teacher reviews, adds grade & feedback

Versioning: show previous submissions and re-submit if allowed


Quiz & grading

Auto-grade MCQs, manual-grade essay questions

Show result page with score breakdown

Save incomplete quiz progress (if allowed)


Notifications

Real-time-ish (use WebSocket later; for now simulate with polling or push)

Types: new assignment, grade posted, course announcement, message

Toast notifications for immediate actions + notification center


Search & discovery

Global search for courses, teachers, lessons

Autocomplete suggestions


Offline / caching (basic)

Cache static assets, allow reading previously loaded lessons via localStorage / Cache API (advanced: service worker)



