18 — Nice-to-have / stretch features (if you have extra time)

Rich-text editor for creating lessons (Quill or Draft.js ideas)

Video hosting or embed with timestamps & note-taking

Real-time chat (WebSocket)

Certificates on course completion (PDF)

Gamification: badges & leaderboards

Import/export CSV for grades

Multi-language support (i18n)



---

19 — Visual & copywriting tips (to make it “cool”)

Use short, action-focused CTAs: “Start Learning”, “Preview Lesson”

Use real teacher avatars/photos and course thumbnails

Keep hero copy concise (1–2 lines) + subline

Use microcopy for forms (explain why you need fields)

Use whitespace — modern UI breathes



---

20 — Example UI flow (sample user journey)

1. Guest visits Home → sees featured course → clicks Course Detail.


2. Chooses “Register” → email verification → lands on Student Dashboard.


3. Enrolls in course → clicks “Continue last lesson” → watches lesson, downloads resource.


4. Sees assignment due → uploads submission → gets confirmation toast.


5. Teacher sees pending submission in dashboard → grades it → student receives notification & views feedback.




